summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 25493, entitled "An Ordinance authorizing and directing the City Engineer to incur an indebtedness in an amount not to exceed Five Hundred Eighty and 95/100 Dollars ($580.95) against the General Fund on account of the cost and expense of the construction of a concrete bulkhead in front of Lots Two (2), Three (3), Four (4) and Five (5), Block One (1), and Lots One (1) and Two (2), Block Two (2), Replat of Green Lake Home Addition, as authorized by Ordinance No. 22819," passed over Mayor's veto October 31st, 1910.
